              <span id="reviewTextContainer3204378857" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11720555051813521257">It had to happen, my bookish love affair with Joanne Harris came to a grinding halt with this book, despite it being set in Lansquenet-sous-Tannes where &apos;Chocolat&apos; was set. Any magical realism written by anyone other than Haruki Murakami I struggle to appreciate, and this split narrative (the other narrative is set 20 years earlier in Yorkshire) read, from the point of view of a bottle of Blackberry wine was lost on me. Interestingly I later found out that the American versions have a convention</span>
  <span id="freeText11720555051813521257" style="display:none">It had to happen, my bookish love affair with Joanne Harris came to a grinding halt with this book, despite it being set in Lansquenet-sous-Tannes where 'Chocolat' was set. Any magical realism written by anyone other than Haruki Murakami I struggle to appreciate, and this split narrative (the other narrative is set 20 years earlier in Yorkshire) read, from the point of view of a bottle of Blackberry wine was lost on me. Interestingly I later found out that the American versions have a conventional third person narrator! 2 out of 12.... sorry!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1582531625i/29011367.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="11720555051813521257" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


